{
  "stem": "2539.3",
  "chunk_idx": 18,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the maid used to bring the dishes, and you know, three or four courses.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And one-- and the discussions, and-- and then my father used to lie down, have a little sleep, and then he used to take off and go again somewhere.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I don't know where.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And you know, and we went to do house-- homework or whatever, and or play with friends.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So it was a very, very sedate, very normal, very beautiful, harmonious life-- very beautiful life-- very beautiful life-- family life-- very beautiful family life.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very good relationships.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was never any friction.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember once, I was angry with my mother, because she didn't let me go to a party, because I had a cold.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I thought, what a terrible mother I've got.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She's not letting me go to-- to a party, because I have a cold.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the only incident I remember that I was against my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Through having lost your family so early in your life, how-- how did you actually cope with-- with the thought that you may never see them again, in all the times that you were hiding, all the experiences that you went through?",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Look.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can't describe the trauma, the shock that one gets.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because I went to Lutsk, don't forget, in '44 already, to see whether anyone survived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went when the front was still on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, the night I arrived, and went back to the solicitor and his wife, with my little bundle with extra shoes and change of clothes, I had to leave, because the Germans took over the-- the town again that night.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I had to leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
